      "side": 1,
      "message": "It would definitely be more correct to call glFinish if the host does not support sync, but if it doesn\u0027t, the host driver is older than OpenGL 3.2, which seems to mean that its driver updates have ended in 2009 (refs: https://www.opengl.org/sdk/docs/man/html/glFenceSync.xhtml, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenGL#OpenGL_3.1).\n\nSo, I\u0027d be up for adding a check for this in a future CL, but I don\u0027t think the vast majority of users will have issues with OOO frames if we just use what we have right now.\n\nIn terms of testing: sync fence support definitely exists and works on all the dev / personal machines I tested emulator on so far. (windows nvidia 320.xx, 36x.xx, mac os x intel iris, linux nvidia 340.xx)",
