      "writtenOn": "2016-08-10T05:46:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah I\u0027ve not actually seen this line (this function, really...) fire very much if at all in testing, but I thought it would be nice to clean it up in case we get some shorter lived context that uses sync, and then when that context is destroyed, and some other long lived context is created that doesn\u0027t use sync, we don\u0027t want to leave the sync thread there. Yeah, that is a far fetched situation based on what I\u0027ve seen so far, since the situations where the 1:1 thread:context invariant has been broken seem to be rare if they exist at all, for the emulator use case at least.\n\nThere\u0027s not much evidence-based justification for putting this here, but it seems reasonable to do so, and it is in line with the logic of destroying the render context. Plus, there\u0027s no harm of destroying it too early, since all sync creations will check for and create a sync thread if one does not exist. So, I vote to leave this here anyway, to handle that hypothetical case, and to keep the logic consistent.",
