      "writtenOn": "2016-08-10T05:46:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It doesn\u0027t seem to have caused any performance problems (glFlush might actually help performance in some cases if the driver is improperly delaying a command), but if this flush call is not there, the underlying host driver might do this:\n\nRender thread A:\n\nIssues eglCreateSyncKHR\n\nRender thread B:\n\nIssues eglClientWaitSyncKHR (waiting on the one in A)\n\nIf no glFlush:\n\nRender thread A\u0027s command is not put in the GPU queue for a while, sitting in some intermediate driver queue, for whatever mysterious driver reasons.\n\nRender thread B\u0027s eglClientWaitSyncKHR chances are, is called with the FLUSH_COMMANDS bitfield flag, so it immediately goes to the GPU queue.\n\nThen the GPU queue looks like this:\n\nback | eglCreateSyncKHR | ... maybe some other commands ... |eglClientWaitSyncKHR | front\n\nThis is a deadlock, because eglClientWaitSyncKHR is waiting on something that will complete after it itself is completed.",
      "parentUuid": "1919df0e_eadc6a14",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 668,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 668,
